<TITLE> Kabir Chowdhury to head new education committee </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Mustak Ahmed bdnews24.com correspondent Dhaka, Apr 5 (bdnews24.com)The government is forming a committee to recommend a new national education policy with professor Kabir Chowdhury as its chief, according to the education secretary. The proposal has been sent to the prime minister and will be finalised after her approval, Syed Ataur Rahman said. The education policy will be based on Kudrat-e-Khuda Education Commission and modernised in line with Dr Shamsul Alam Education Policy. A proposal of a 16-member committee has been sent to the prime minister, said an official at the education ministry, preferring to remain unnamed. This committee, to be known as Kabir Chowdhury committee, will have three months for the job, he said. Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid spoke about a new education policy in the next few months in a workshop on Mar 17. He said essential topics of the previous governments' education commissions would be included in the new policy. No recommendations of the education commissions formed before or after independence were implemented to date. b
